[[File:ROM-Eth1.jpg|thumb|[[Somalis|Somali]] man of Eastern [[Hamitic]] type (sculpture of ''[[The Races of Mankind]]'' series, 1929).]] '''Ethiopid''' (also spelled '''Aethiopid''', '''Erythriote''') is a historical [[Race (human classification)|racial classification]] of humans. It was equivalent with the [[Hamites|Eastern Hamite]] division of the [[Caucasian race]].<ref name="Baker">{{cite book|last1=Baker|first1=John Randal|title=Race|date=1974|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=0192129546|pages=225-226|url=https://www.google.com/books/about/Race.html?id=PD-BAAAAMAAJ|accessdate=28 May 2018}}</ref><ref>''Meyers Konversationslexikon'' 4th ed. (Leipzig, 1885–1890), [[:File:Meyers b11 s0476a.jpg|ethnographic map]].</ref>
==Origin, distribution and physiognomy== Ethiopids are typically classified as a [[Caucasian race|Caucasoid]] (Europid) subrace.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Simpson|first1=George Eaton|last2=Yinger|first2=J. Milton|title=The Meaning of Race|journal=Racial and Cultural Minorities|date=1985|pages=27-39|url=https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-1-4899-0551-2_2|accessdate=28 May 2018}}</ref> According to [[John Baker (biologist)|John Baker]] (1974), in their stable form, their center of distribution was considered to be [[Horn of Africa]], among that region's [[Afroasiatic languages|Hamito-Semitic]]-speaking populations.<ref name="Baker"/>
Physically, the classic Ethiopid was of medium height, with a dolicocephalic or mesocephalic skull (see [[cephalic index]]). Facial form was essentially Caucasoid, with an orthognathic profile (no [[prognathism]]) and a rather prominent, narrow nose. Hair form was often ringlety and skin color was invariably brown, with either a reddish or blackish tinge. It is not certain which Caucasoid subrace formed the basis of this stock, but authorities usually suggested [[Mediterranean race|Mediterranid]] or Proto-Mediterranid ancestors.<ref name="Baker"/>
==See also== *[[Caucasoid]] *[[Hamitic]] *[[People of Ethiopia]] *[[Arabid race|Arabid]] *[[Mediterranean race|Mediterranid]] *[[Brown (racial classification)|Brown race]]
