{{Infobox venue | name = The Bolshoi Drama Theatre, Second Stage | nickname = Kamenny Island Theatre | native_name = Каменноостровский театр, вторая сцена БДТ | native_name_lang = | fullname = | former names = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = Kamennoostrovsky Theatre 1.jpg | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = Kamenny Island Theatre | pushpin_map = | pushpin_mapsize = | pushpin_map_caption = | pushpin_label_position = | address = Old Theatre Sq. 13, [[St. Petersburg]], [[Russia]] | location = | coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LON|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | type = | genre = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1826 | renovated = 1843, 1964 - 1967, 2006 - 2012 | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = [[Tovstonogov Bolshoi Drama Theatre]] | surface = | scoreboard = | production = | cost = | architect = [[Smaragd Shustov]], [[Alberto Cavos]] | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | seating_type = | capacity = 310 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | field_shape = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|www.bdt.spb.ru}} --> | publictransit = }}
The '''Kamenny Island Theatre''' (also known as the '''Stone Island Theatre''', in Russian: Каменноостровский театр) is a wooden theatre on the grounds of the [[Kamennoostrovsky Palace]], [[Kamenny Island]], [[Saint Petersburg]], [[Russia]]. It is the only surviving wooden theatre in [[Saint Petersburg|St. Petersburg]], and one of the few remaining in [[Europe]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rtgtv.com/films/688/|title=Films & ProgramsThe wooden theatre on Kamenny Island – details & schedule – RTG TV|website=rtgtv.com|access-date=2016-09-25}}</ref> The theatre is a world heritage site protected by [[UNESCO]].<ref>{{Cite book|title=Baltic Piling|last=Mets, Raudsepp|first=|publisher=CRC Press|year=2013|isbn=1315879549|location=|pages=50|via=Google Books}}</ref>
Since 2005, the theatre is home to a second stage of the [[Tovstonogov Bolshoi Drama Theater|Bolshoi Drama]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fontanka.ru/2007/03/14/082/|title=У БДТ тоже появится "вторая сцена"|access-date=2016-09-25}}</ref>
==History of the building== The theatre was built in 1826 to a design by [[Smaragd Shustov]] in just 40 days. The building was intended to stand for seven years, but it survived much more. In 1843, [[Alberto Cavos]] was commissioned to develop a new project. Reconstruction of the theatre has principally changes the building's outlook, but the auditorium received only minor changes.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://bdt.spb.ru/%D1%81%D1%85%D0%B5%D0%BC%D0%B0-%D0%BF%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B5%D0%B7%D0%B4%D0%B0/%D0%BA%D0%B0%D0%BC%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B2%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B8%D0%B9-%D1%82%D0%B5%D0%B0%D1%82%D1%80/|title=Каменноостровский театр|last=|first=|date=|website=БДТ|publisher=|access-date=}}</ref> In 1964-1967, the venue was restorated according to a project overseen by [[Irina Benois]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bdt.spb.ru/%D1%81%D1%85%D0%B5%D0%BC%D0%B0-%D0%BF%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B5%D0%B7%D0%B4%D0%B0/%D0%BA%D0%B0%D0%BC%D0%B5%D0%BD%D0%BD%D0%BE%D0%BE%D1%81%D1%82%D1%80%D0%BE%D0%B2%D1%81%D0%BA%D0%B8%D0%B9-%D1%82%D0%B5%D0%B0%D1%82%D1%80/|title=Каменноостровский театр|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=БДТ|access-date=}}</ref> Although the facade of the theatre was kept intact, the auditorium was completely rearranged. After the reconstruction, the theatre was made property of the [[Petersburg – Channel 5|St. Petersburg Television Company]]. In 2005, a decree of the [[President of Russia]] has transferred the Kamenny Island Theatre to the [[Tovstonogov Bolshoi Drama Theater|Bolshoi Drama Theatre]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fontanka.ru/2012/01/29/030/|title=Каменноостровский театр - зрителям вход воспрещен|access-date=2016-09-25}}</ref> Extensive renovation took place in between 2005 and 2012, when the theatre has opened as the second stage of the Bolshoi Drama.<ref name=":0" />
