'''Maher''' or Mahrem is a god of the [[Kingdom of Aksum|Aksumites]] and the [[Himyarites]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Duchesne|first=Louis|title=The churches separated from Rome|year=1907|publisher=International Catholic Library|location=Westmonasterii}}</ref> He was the son of the main god [[Astar (god)|Ashtar]], and his counterpart was Beher, god of the sea. He was the [[deity]] of war, comparable to [[Mars (mythology)|Mars]] or [[Ares]] in ancient [[Greek mythology]], who used both forms [[Interpretatio Graeca|of the interpretatio]]. The God ''Maher'' (or Mahrem) held a place of special importance with the Axumites; the gods of the pagan period were all called the Sons of the Invincible Mahrem.<ref>{{cite book|last=Duchesne|first=Louis|title=The churches separated from Rome|year=1907|publisher=International Catholic Library|location=Westmonasterii}}</ref>

