{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2012}} {{Infobox software | name = Sports Tracker | logo = <!-- image --> | screenshot = <!-- Image name is enough --> | caption = | developer = Sports Tracking Technologies Ltd. | released = 2004 | latest release version = | latest release date = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} --> | status = Active | programming language = | operating system = [[iOS]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]], [[BlackBerry OS|Blackberry]], [[Windows Phone]], [[Symbian]], [[MeeGo]] | size = | genre = [[Health informatics]], [[Physical fitness]] | license = [[Freemium]] | website = {{URL|https://www.sports-tracker.com}} }}
'''Sports Tracker''', earlier ''Nokia Sports Tracker'' was originally a software tool for [[S60 (software platform)|Symbian Series 60]] phones (particularly those that included a [[Global Positioning System|GPS]] facility such as the [[Nokia N95]], or bluetooth phones with the addition of a bluetooth-compatible GPS receiver) that allowed its user to track their route, speed, timings and energy expenditure,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pocket-lint.co.uk/reviews/review.phtml/3324 |title= Nokia Sports Tracker - Looking for a personal trainer? |publisher=pocket-lint.co.uk }}</ref> while engaging in a sport activity such as [[running]], [[jogging]] or [[cycling]].<ref name="stuff.tv">{{cite web |url=http://stuff.tv/blogs/sport/archive/2008/06/26/nokia-sports-tracker.aspx |title=Nokia Sports Tracker review |work=Stuff.tv|publisher=Haymarket Media Group}}</ref>
Nokia announced that Nokia Sports Tracker was closed in June 2010,<ref>[https://sportstracker.nokia.com/nts Announcement of Closure and Transfer] {{webarchive|url=http://arquivo.pt/wayback/20110707172739/http%3A//sportstracker.nokia.com/nts |date=7 July 2011 }}, Nokia</ref> but the application was continued by Sports Tracking Technologies Ltd. simply as ''Sports Tracker'', which was set up by three people from the team in Nokia. It is now available for [[iPhone]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[Windows Phone]] devices and allows its user to track and analyze their performance, and to share workout data and photos with its friends.<ref>[http://www.arcticstartup.com/article/sports-tracker-coming-to-iphone-and-android Sports Tracker Coming To iPhone And Android]</ref><ref>[http://www.sports-tracker.com/blog/2011/12/16/sports-tracker-now-available-for-windows-phone-win-a-nokia-lumia-800/ Sports Tracker now available for Windows Phone + win a Nokia Lumia 800!]</ref>
On 4 May 2015, [[Amer Sports]] announced having acquired Sports Tracker.<ref>(Press Release) http://www.amersports.com/newsroom/news/news-article/2015/05/04/amer-sports-strengthens-its-digital-connectivity-services-and-capabilities-through-acquisition-of-sports-tracker-</ref>
