{{Infobox television channel | name = TiVi5MONDE | logofile = | logosize = | logocaption = | logoalt = Logo of the channel. | launch = {{ubl|{{Start date and age|2012|1}} (United States)|{{Start date and age|2016|6|11}} (Africa)}} | closed date = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | picture format = [[576i]] '''[[SDTV]]''' | share = | share as of = | share source = | owner = TV5MONDE, S.A. | slogan = ''Let the fun begin… en français!'' | country = {{ubl|[[France]]|[[Belgium]]|[[Switzerland]]|[[Canada]]}} | language = [[French language|French]] | broadcast area = {{ubl|[[United States]]|[[Americas]] & [[Africa]]}} | affiliates = {{ubl|TiVi5MONDE USA|TiVi5MONDE Afrique}} | headquarters = [[Paris]], France | former names = | replaced names = | replaced by names = | sister names = {{ubl|[[TV5MONDE]]|TV5MONDE Cinéma|TV5MONDE Style|[[TV5 Québec Canada|TV5]]|[[Unis (TV channel)|Unis]]}} | timeshift names = | website = {{URL|www.tivi5mondeplus.com}} | terr serv 1 = [[Digital terrestrial television|DTT]] (Ghana) | terr chan 1 = Check local listings (SD) | sat serv 1 = [[Dish Network]] (U.S.) | sat chan 1 = Check local listings (SD) | sat serv 2 = [[DirecTV]] (U.S.) | sat chan 2 = Channel 118 (SD) | sat serv 3 = [[Canalsat Horizons]] (African Union) | sat chan 3 = Channel 274 (SD) | sat serv 4 = [[SES S.A.|SES-4]] (African Union) | sat chan 4 = Check local listings (SD) | cable serv 1 = | cable chan 1 = | sat radio serv 1 = | sat radio chan 1 = | iptv serv 1 = | iptv chan 1 = | online serv 1 = TiVi5MONDE Plus | online chan 1 = [http://www.tivi5mondeplus.com Watch online] (SD) | 3gmobile serv 1 = }}
'''TiVi5 Monde''' ({{IPA-fr|ti vi sɛ̃k mɔ̃d}}), stylized as '''TiVi5 MONDE''', is a television channel launched at the end of January 2012<ref name=":2">{{Cite web|url=http://www.consulfrance-miami.org/spip.php?article3079|title=Tivi5 Monde, la première télé en français dédiée au jeune public|last=Gratta|first=Laura|date=May 17, 2012|website=Miami's French Consulate website|publisher=|language=French|access-date=December 25, 2016}}</ref> by the [[Francophonie|Francophone]] channel [[TV5 Monde]], which is aimed mainly to [[French language|French-speaking]] [[Africa]]n children (4–13 years).<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=http://actualite.housseniawriting.com/afrique/2016/06/13/chaine-tivi5-monde-afrique/16241|title=La chaîne TiVi5 Monde arrive en Afrique|last=Nguema|first=Boubakar|date=2016|work=Actualité Houssenia Writing|language=French|access-date=December 25, 2016|via=}}</ref> The objective of the channel is to teach French to young children through dedicated programs.<ref name=":1" />
== History == === 2012: American launch === Tivi5Monde is the first [[America]]n channel and the only one to date targeting only children with a 24/7 program entirely in [[French language|French]]. This new channel is available on [[Dish Network]] and is part of the "Bouquet français" offering [[TV5 Monde]].<ref name=":2" />
=== 2016: African launch === On {{Start date|2016|6|11}}, TiVi5 Monde, the [[TV5 Monde]] channel dedicated to children, is launched in [[Africa]]. Already broadcast in the [[United States]] since 2012, it is now hosting African productions and broadcasting in some forty countries over Africa.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://www.jeuneafrique.com/332445/economie/media-tivi5-monde-chaine-petits-francophones-debarque-afrique/|title=TiVi5 Monde, la chaîne des petits francophones, débarque en Afrique|last=Godet|first=Aurélie|date=June 10, 2016|work=Jeune Afrique|language=French|access-date=December 25, 2016|via=}}</ref>
While TV5 Monde targets adults, TiVi5 Monde targets children. "In order to children choose [[French language|French]], it is necessary to support this language in Africa", explains Yves Bigot, CEO of TV5 Monde.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":0" />
The channel started broadcasting [[free-to-air]] on the SES4 satellite and is made accessible on channel 274 of [[Canalsat|Canalsat Horizons]]. It is sponsored by [[Dominique Ouattara]], first lady of [[Côte d'Ivoire]] and president of the Children of Africa Foundation.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":0" />
The content already offered by TiVi5 Monde to young [[America]]ns since 2012 has not changed, with only one difference: 12% of the productions broadcast are African.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":0" />
The channel had however to be satisfied with a modest budget. The initially announced amount of 1.4 million euros has been revised downwards as several expected financings have not arrived. It is therefore necessary to find a rational economic model :<ref name=":1" /> the channel's responsibles decided to pool TiVi5 Monde Afrique with that already active in the United States. The same programs are broadcast on both continents.<ref name=":0" />
== Programing == TiVi5 Monde airs educational programs, cartoons, children's series and games. Starting 2012, 12% of the productions broadcast in the channel are [[Africa]]n. All the programs are 100% [[French language|French-speaking]]; the channel doesn't make any French dubbing of [[America]]n series.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":0" /> Its programs both playful and educational are broadcast without advertising.<ref name=":2" />
